 4.Text formatting and operations using String Function in php 
Program Code: 
String.php 
<?php 
$text = "Hello World"; 
?> 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
<title>String Functions in PHP</title> 
<style> 
 body { 
 font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
 background: #f8f9fa; 
 } 
 .container { 
 width: 50%; 
 margin: 40px auto; 
 background: white; 
 padding: 20px; 
 border-radius: 10px; 
 border: 1px solid #ccc; 
 box-shadow: 0px 3px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); 
 } 
 h2 { 
 text-align: center; 
 color: #007bff; 
 } 
 table { 
 width: 100%; 
 border-collapse: collapse; 
 margin-top: 15px; 
 } 
 th, td { 
 border: 1px solid #999; 
 padding: 8px; 
 text-align: center; 
 } 
 th { 
 background: #007bff;
 color: white; 
 } 
 td { 
 background: #f4f6f7; 
 } 
</style> 
</head> 
<body> 
<div class="container"> 
 <h2>String Functions in PHP</h2> 
 <table> 
 <tr> 
 <th>Operation</th> 
 <th>Result</th> 
 </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Original Text</td> 
 <td><?php echo $text; ?></td> 
 </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Uppercase</td> 
 <td><?php echo strtoupper($text); ?></td>  </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Lowercase</td> 
 <td><?php echo strtolower($text); ?></td>  </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Length</td> 
 <td><?php echo strlen($text); ?></td> 
 </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Reversed</td> 
 <td><?php echo strrev($text); ?></td> 
 </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Replace 'World' with 'PHP'</td> 
 <td><?php echo str_replace("World", "PHP", $text); ?></td>  </tr> 
 <tr> 
 <td>Substring (first 5 letters)</td>
 <td><?php echo substr($text, 0, 5); ?></td> 
 </tr> 
 </table> 
</div> 
</body> 
</html> 
Output:

 5.Student grade calculation using Arrays and Functions in php 
Program Code: 
Array.php 
<?php 
// Function to calculate grade 
function calculateGrade($marks) { 
if ($marks >= 90) { 
 return "A"; 
} elseif ($marks >= 75) { 
 return "B"; 
} elseif ($marks >= 50) { 
 return "C"; 
} else { 
 return "F"; 
} 
} 
// Array of students with marks 
$students = array( 
"John" => 85, 
"Mary" => 92, 
"Peter" => 67, 
"Anita" => 45 
); 
?> 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
<title>Student Grade Calculation</title> 
<style> 
 body { 
 font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
 background: #f8f9fa; 
 } 
 .container { 
 width: 60%; 
 margin: 40px auto; 
 background: #fff; 
 padding: 20px; 
 border-radius: 10px;
 border: 1px solid #ddd; 
 box-shadow: 0px 3px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);  } 
 h2 { 
 text-align: center; 
 color: #007bff; 
 } 
 table { 
 width: 100%; 
 border-collapse: collapse; 
 margin-top: 15px; 
 } 
 th, td { 
 border: 1px solid #999; 
 padding: 10px; 
 text-align: center; 
 } 
 th { 
 background: #007bff; 
 color: white; 
 } 
 td { 
 background: #f4f6f7; 
 } 
 .gradeA { color: green; font-weight: bold; }  .gradeB { color: blue; font-weight: bold; }  .gradeC { color: orange; font-weight: bold; }  .gradeF { color: red; font-weight: bold; } </style> 
</head> 
<body> 
<div class="container"> 
 <h2>Student Grades</h2> 
 <table> 
 <tr> 
 <th>Student</th> 
 <th>Marks</th> 
 <th>Grade</th> 
 </tr> 
 <?php 
 foreach ($students as $name => $marks) {
 $grade = calculateGrade($marks); 
 $class = "grade" . $grade; 
 ?> 
 <tr> 
 <td><?php echo $name; ?></td> 
 <td><?php echo $marks; ?></td> 
 <td class="<?php echo $class; ?>"><?php echo $grade; ?></td>  </tr> 
 <?php } ?> 
 </table> 
</div> 
</body> 
</html> 
Output:

 6.Online registration Form Handling using php 
Program Code: 
Registration.php 
<?php 
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") { // Collect form data 
$name = $_POST['name']; 
$email = $_POST['email']; 
$password = $_POST['password']; 
?> 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
<title>Registration Result</title> 
<style> 
 body { 
 font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
 background: #f8f9fa; 
 } 
 .container { 
 width: 40%; 
 margin: 50px auto; 
 background: #fff; 
 padding: 20px; 
 border-radius: 10px; 
 border: 1px solid #ccc; 
 box-shadow: 0px 3px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); 
 text-align: center; 
 } 
 h2 { color: green; } 
 p { font-size: 16px; } 
</style> 
</head> 
